<section id="about" style="background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.8); color: white;">
  <div class="center-block col-md-10" style="padding-top: 5%; padding-bottom: 5%;">
    <h1 class="text-center" style="font-size: 50px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 2%;">Our Mission</h1>
    <hr class="hr fW" style="margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
    <div class="post2">
      <h4 style="display: inline-block; text-align: center; font-weight: 200; line-height: 1.3">
        Our mission is to bring light to the lives of those who have walked through life in a bicultural, or even multicultural household. We feel that there is much to be learned from these unique perspectives and accordingly, we seek out unique ways to address this topic. We have found, however, that these perspectives lack any tangible form and organization. Within the Korean community of Greater Vancouver, there seems to be a disconnect between the first generation of immigrants and the second, leading to a vague sense of cultural identity--this is where Modni steps in. We would like to give form to the myriad of variables that comprise a bicultural identity, starting with Korean-Canadians. From there, we’d like to delve in deeper to see what significance this has on our lives, and ultimately reconnect the two generations.
      </h4>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="post1" style="margin-top: 6%; margin-bottom: 6%;">Want to learn more about us?<br />Press the button below.
      </h2>
      <a class="btn btn-lg btn-danger button" style="margin-bottom: 20px;" href="<%= about_path  %>">About Us !</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
